


Java 14 Features (Interview Important + Examples)

Java 14 introduced several productivity and modern language enhancements, especially for writing cleaner code.

1. Records (Preview in Java 14) ⭐
..................................
Records are used to create immutable data carrier classes (DTOs) with minimal code.

Without Records
..................................
public class Employee {

    private int id;
    private String name;

    public Employee(int id, String name) {
        this.id = id;
        this.name = name;
    }

    public int getId() { return id; }
    public String getName() { return name; }
}
With Records (Java 14)
..............................
public record Employee(
        int id,
        String name) {
}
Usage
Employee emp =
        new Employee(101, "Sunil");

System.out.println(emp.id());
System.out.println(emp.name());
Benefits

✔ Less boilerplate code
✔ Immutable by default
✔ Auto-generated constructor, getters, equals, hashCode

2. Switch Expression (Final in Java 14) ⭐
....................................
Makes switch more powerful and cleaner.

Before Java 14
int day = 2;
String result;

switch (day) {
    case 1:
        result = "Monday";
        break;
    case 2:
        result = "Tuesday";
        break;
    default:
        result = "Invalid";
}
Java 14 Switch Expression
..........................
int day = 2;

String result =
        switch (day) {
            case 1 -> "Monday";
            case 2 -> "Tuesday";
            default -> "Invalid";
        };
Output
Tuesday
Benefits

✔ No break statements
✔ Cleaner syntax
✔ Returns values directly

3. Pattern Matching for instanceof (Preview)
..............................................
Simplifies type casting.

Before Java 14
Object obj = "Java";

if (obj instanceof String) {
    String s = (String) obj;
    System.out.println(s);
}
Java 14
Object obj = "Java";

if (obj instanceof String s) {
    System.out.println(s);
}
Benefits

✔ No explicit casting
✔ Less boilerplate

4. Helpful NullPointerException Messages
.....................................................
Java 14 improves debugging.

Example
Employee emp = null;

emp.getName();
Output (Improved Error)
Exception in thread "main"
java.lang.NullPointerException:
Cannot invoke "Employee.getName()"
because "emp" is null
Benefits

✔ Easier debugging
✔ Shows exact null reference

5. Text Blocks (Preview in earlier versions, improved usage)
....................................................
Used for multi-line strings.

Example
String json = """
{
    "id": 101,
    "name": "Sunil"
}
""";

System.out.println(json);
Benefits

✔ Cleaner JSON/XML handling
✔ No escape characters

Real-Time Example (Spring Boot DTO)
Using Record as DTO
public record EmployeeDTO(
        int id,
        String name,
        double salary) {
}
Controller
@GetMapping("/employee")
public EmployeeDTO getEmployee() {

    return new EmployeeDTO(
            101,
            "Sunil",
            50000);
}
Output
{
  "id": 101,
  "name": "Sunil",
  "salary": 50000
}
Interview Summary
Feature	Description
Records	Compact immutable DTOs
Switch Expressions	Functional switch
Pattern Matching instanceof	No casting needed
Helpful NPE Messages	Better debugging
Text Blocks	Multi-line strings

